quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  2,38,"We said, \"Get ye down from it, all together: and if Guidance shall come to you from me, whoso shall follow my guidance, on them shall come no fear, neither shall they be grieved"
  2,39,"But they who shall not believe, and treat our signs as false-hoods, these shall be inmates of the fire; in it shall they remain for ever"
  2,40,"O children of Israel! remember my favour wherewith I shewed favour upon you, and be true to your covenant with me; I will be true to my covenant with you; me therefore, revere me"
  2,41,"and believe in what I have sent down confirming your Scriptures, and be not the first to disbelieve it, neither for a mean price barter my signs: me therefore, fear ye me"
  2,42,"And clothe not the truth with falsehood, and hide not the truth when ye know it"
  2,43,"And observe prayer and pay the legal impost, and bow down with those who bow"
  2,44,"Will ye enjoin what is right upon others, and forget yourselves? Yet ye read the Book: will ye not understand"
  2,45,"And seek help with patience and prayer: a hard duty indeed is this, but not to the humble"
  2,46,"Who bear in mind that they shall meet their Lord, and that unto Him shall they return"
  2,47,O children of Israel! remember my favour wherewith I shewed favour upon you; for verily to you above all human beings have I been bounteous
  2,48,"And fear ye the day when soul shall not satisfy for soul at all, nor shall any intercession be accepted from them, nor shall any ransom be taken, neither shall they be helped"